1
00:00:00,720 --> 00:00:04,270
Here's a bit of trivia about how
network people think of their systems.

2
00:00:04,270 --> 00:00:07,270
If you do a traceroute and look through
the host names of some of the hops

3
00:00:07,270 --> 00:00:12,133
between you and some other site, you may
often see three letter codes like, sea,

4
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:18,100
here, or, sjc lax, here.

5
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:20,647
These are not arbitrary names,
they're airport codes.

6
00:00:20,647 --> 00:00:26,696
Network operators often name large nodes
of their network after nearby airports.

7
00:00:26,696 --> 00:00:28,790
It makes it easier to keep
track of them geographically.
